      "content": "You should absolutely not change your dosage without consulting your prescribing physician, even if you feel great. Warfarin dosing is highly individualized, and what feels \"steady\" to you might be dangerously unstable for your specific clotting profile. A sudden drop could put you at risk for clots, which is the exact thing you are trying to prevent with this medication. Your doctor needs to monitor your INR levels to make any adjustments safely.",
